  "prompt": "What is \"Midwest\"?",
  "response": "The term \"Midwest\" typically refers to the Midwestern United States, a region that includes several states in the central part of the country. The Midwest is often characterized by its diverse economy, agriculture, manufacturing, and known for its cultural heritage and friendly communities. The states commonly included in the Midwest are:\n\n- Illinois\n- Indiana\n- Iowa\n- Kansas\n- Michigan\n- Minnesota\n- Missouri\n- Nebraska\n- North Dakota\n- Ohio\n- South Dakota\n- Wisconsin\n\nThis region is also home to major cities such as Chicago, Detroit, Cleveland, Minneapolis, and St. Louis. The Midwest is known for its distinct seasons, including cold winters and hot summers, as well as its contributions to American culture, industry, and politics.",
